                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 15984/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. O’Brien, referring to the department’s telegrams of October 9 and 10,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d491fn1">Not printed.</note> concerning the arrest of
                    Yoshitaro Abe, informs Mr. Root that, as the man is Japanese, the foreign office
                    requests assurance that the United States will reciprocate under similar
                    circumstances in the future. Mr. O’Brien refers to Mr. Griscom’s No. 23, dated
                    November, 1903.<note n="1" xml:id="d491fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
